WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.000
T-house is one of Laos Shu'a's most famous plays. He wrote it in 1957.

00:09.000 --> 00:20.000
The play has three acts and shows the lives of common people in China from the end of the 19th century to the middle of the 20th century.

00:20.000 --> 00:27.000
It tells us the story of Wang Li-Fa and the customers of his T-house in Beijing.

00:28.000 --> 00:38.000
It describes the changes in Chinese society over 50 years. Laos Shu'a was born in Beijing in 1899.

00:38.000 --> 00:50.000
His mother sent him to a teacher's school in 1913. After finishing school in 1918, he became a head teacher of a primary school.

00:50.000 --> 01:03.000
In 1924, Laos Shu'a left home and went to England. He taught Chinese at a college in London and returned to China five years later.

01:03.000 --> 01:12.000
He wrote many plays, novels and short stories about people's lives and was named the People's Artist.

01:12.000 --> 01:19.000
Laos Shu'a is one of the greatest Chinese writers of the 20th century.

01:20.000 --> 01:27.000
At Laos Shu'a T-house today, customers can drink tea and eat delicious Beijing food.

01:27.000 --> 01:36.000
If you like the Beijing Opera, traditional music or magic shows, you can enjoy them at the T-house.

01:36.000 --> 01:42.000
Laos Shu'a T-house gives a warm welcome to everyone from all over the world.

